# "Quirell" Social Network Project

---

## Running Locally

This section **assumes you are running a Linux distrubution**,
specifically Ubuntu. The code will probably run on something other
than that, but no promises! Beyond that requirement, you also need
to have basic familiarity with:

* [python 3.4](https://www.python.org/)
* [git](http://git-scm.com/)

You can get python 3.4 via:

    $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:fkrull/deadsnakes
    $ sudo apt-get update
    $ sudo apt-get install python3.4

And git via:

    $ sudo apt-get install git

Then you obtain the source code with

    $ git clone git@gitlab.com:collectqt/quirell.git

---
